<TABLE BGCOLOR=#ccffff WIDTH=60% BORDER=0 BORDERCOLOR=#0000ff> <TR><TD><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3" COLOR="#000000"><FONT SIZE=-1> <A NAME=POST700>  By <B><!-Email-!><A HREF="javascript:alert('The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.')" onMouseOver="window.status = 'The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.'; return true"><!-/Email-!><!-Name-!>Jabor<!-/Name-!></A></B> on Friday, January 5, 2001 - 02:24 am:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><P> <!-Text-!> Sonn Ultok Kin, <BR> <BR>this be jabor, i have since departed from the world of everquest, but i have learned of a new world that methinks might be of intrest ta some of tha axepeak dwarves, Shadowbane. <BR> <BR>in case you and the kin are unaware shadowbane is all pvp but will not be random pking since everyone will be in a guild and if you kill someone you better hope your guild can take on there guild and protect you.  well me and some of my friends at college are already talking about starting dwarves and grouping together, but if we ever hoped to own a city we would need massive support so that is why i come to the brothers.  shadowbane is sounding like it will be an excellant mmorpg, it will have a soft cap not hard cap meaning you can reach it in a month or so and be able to pvp and explore to your hearts content.  you can still level but the rewards will diminish.  weapons will not be as important as the skills your char has.  also you can have land ownership and i am hoping we can get an all dwarf town, although it will be hard, but i believe it is a worthy goal. <BR> <BR>pros to being a dwarf in sb:  while all the other races learn blacksmithing we can learn forgemastery which should far excel it.  there is a discipline called giant killer that is exclusive to us and only us. <BR> <BR>cons:  no females, sorry dimond and emberlass and all ye other dwarf lasses out there.  classes limited to warrior, crusader&#40;pally&#41;, priest and prelate.  not out yet :&#40;  Spring 2001&#40;hopefully&#41; <BR> <BR>well if this has got your interest go to www.shadowbane.com or <BR>shadowbane.godgames.com &#60;-faster mirror imho <BR> <BR>there is a lot of info out there already and a lot more to come.  most is more of a roleplaying background now for everything with no concrete details but they are a good read. <BR> <BR>hope to get a cheerful response to this. <BR> <BR>Fallen Paladin of Clan Axepeak, Jabor <!-/Text-!> <P> 
